gomodel:SYNGO_560  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Extracellular field recordings in hippocampal slices from Munc13-2 KO mice.\n\nFigure 1 shows an impaired input-output curves indicating impaired synaptic transmission at mossy fiber synapses in the absence of Munc13-2. Synaptic transmission at the Schaffer-collateral synapses recorded in stratum radiatum of area CA1 is not impaired.\nFigure 2 shows that the loss of Munc13-2 leads to increased failures in mossy fiber synaptic transmission.\nFigure 3 shows increased short-term synaptic plasticity in Munc13-2 KO mossy fiber synapses.\nFigure 6 shows that the loss of Munc13-2 leads to a reduction in release probability at mossy fiber synapses.. Experimental description: hippocampal slices were. prepared from littermate wild-type (WT) and Munc13-2-/- (KO) mice, aged between postnatal days P 18-35. The mice were previously described (Varoqueaux et al., 2002)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_560" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

